title: Frieze, 1890–1920
description: A repeating art nouveau design of geometric cartouches containing a linear flower abstraction. Connected by elongated frets to a smaller complementary cartouche alternately framed on the bottom and top by vine on a ground that becomes darker towards the base with a linear overall design between horizontal banded borders. Printed in olive green, taupe, beige, bronze, gold and dark brown.

tombstone.epitaph:
Frieze, 1890–1920.
1890–1920. Machine-printed. Gift of Victorian Collectibles. 1979-91-59.
